{"action":"opened","number":56319,"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/56319","id":2144093709,"node_id":"PR_kwDOABkWpM5_zEYN","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/56319","diff_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/56319.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/56319.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/56319","number":56319,"state":"open","locked":false,"title":"Put `jl_gc_new_weakref` in a header file again","user":{"login":"lgoettgens","id":26390525,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI2MzkwNTI1","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/26390525?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/lgoettgens","html_url":"https://github.com/lgoettgens","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lgoettgens/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lgoettgens/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lgoettgens/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lgoettgens/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lgoettgens/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lgoettgens/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lgoettgens/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lgoettgens/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lgoettgens/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"The gcext implementation in [gap](https://github.com/gap-system/gap/)/[GAP.jl](https://github.com/oscar-system/GAP.jl) uses `jl_gc_new_weakref`. Since https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/55608 got merged, this symbol is no longer mentioned in any header file, and thus the compilation of gap fails. This PR puts it back into a header file, but now in `gc-common.h` (instead of `gc-interface.h`), since https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/55608 moved the implementation to `gc-common.c`.

We are aware of the alternative function `jl_gc_new_weakref_th` (that still is in a header after https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/55608). However, it was not present in any header file before https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/55256, even though it was already marked as `JL_DLLEXPORT` well before that.

In short, without this PR we are not able to adapt the code to a way that works both with julia 1.11 and nightly.

@fingolfin I get locally still the same error as we can observe in CI. I suppose that this needs a rebuild of `libjulia` with this PR here included to work, right? 

